                <p>Fellowship in Family Medicine is an advanced training program that allows family physicians to develop specialized skills in a particular area of interest within the broad field of family medicine. These fellowships provide in-depth training that goes beyond the scope of general family medicine residency. Fellows work under the guidance of experienced mentors, gaining hands-on experience, engaging in research, and participating in academic activities. The goal is to equip physicians with the knowledge and skills to provide more specialized care, contribute to healthcare innovation, and often, take on leadership roles within their communities or healthcare organizations.</p>

